# Lab 001 – VLANs and 802.1Q Trunking

## Overview

In this lab, I configured two physical Cisco Catalyst switches to communicate using an 802.1Q trunk link. The objective was to create VLANs, establish a trunk connection, verify VLAN propagation, and gain hands-on experience working with Cisco IOS.

This lab was completed as part of my CCNA home lab journey using real Cisco hardware.

---

## Objectives

- Configure VLANs on multiple switches
- Configure and verify an 802.1Q trunk
- Allow specific VLANs across the trunk
- Implement a management VLAN
- Practice Cisco IOS verification and troubleshooting commands

---

## Skills Practiced

- VLAN creation and naming
- Trunk configuration
- VLAN propagation
- Spanning Tree verification
- Cisco IOS navigation
- Troubleshooting and validation

---

## Equipment Used

- Cisco WS-C2960S-48TS-S
- Cisco WS-C2960-48PST-S
- USB-to-RJ45 console cable
- Ethernet patch cable
- PuTTY

---

## Lab Status

Completed
